laboratory_examinations.findings: The left lower quadrant of the abdomen demonstrates inflammatory fat stranding and multiple air loculations surrounding a segment of colon with numerous diverticula. The remainder of the colon also demonstrates numerous diverticula. The liver shows a hypoattenuating lesion in the dome, likely a benign cyst. Other abdominal organs are unremarkable. The lung bases show subsegmental atelectasis and a subpleural bleb.
